OL,5, Nigeria's President Bola Tinubu has    
OL,6, announced a six-month increase to the  
OL,7, minimum wage as workers are set to     
OL,8, start an indefinite strike.            
OL,10,FUnions want the monthly wage to be     
OL,11,Fraised to $255 (#210) to help deal with
OL,12,Fthe sharp rise in the cost of living   
OL,13,Fsince Mr Tinubu took office in May.    
OL,15,FThe president's $32 increase only      
OL,16,Fbrings a monthly minimum salary to $70.
OL,18,FHe also pledged to speed up the rollout
OL,19,Fof cheap gas-powered buses to help with
OL,20,Fthe recent tripling of fuel prices.    
